# 📚 Library Management System – Backend Project

A backend system built with Spring Boot for librarians to manage books, members, and borrow/return operations.  
Developed as part of a backend assignment for OneData Software.

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Java 17
- Spring Boot 3.x
- Spring MVC
- PostgreSQL
- JdbcTemplate (Raw SQL)
- JUnit 5
- MockMvc (@Nested, @ParameterizedTest)
- GitLab (Git-Flow)
- Postman (for API testing)

---

## 🔧 Features

### 📘 Book Management
- Add, update, delete, and list books
- Search by title, author, or ISBN
- Tracks availableCopies per book

### 👤 Member Management
- Register, update, and view members
- Stores name, phone, and registration date

### 🔄 Borrow Management
- Lend a book only if copies are available
- Return a book (automatically increases stock)
- Join query returns book + member info in borrow records

### 🚨 Exception Handling
- Global exception handler (@ControllerAdvice)
- Custom errors:
  - ResourceNotFoundException
  - BookAlreadyBorrowedException

### 🧪 Integration Testing
- Tests using MockMvc, @Nested, @ParameterizedTest
- Asserts all response fields and edge cases

---

